Sentencas: The need for high efficiency and low emissions power sources has created significant interest in fuel cells.

Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are desirable for their fuel versatility.

Sentencas: Because high-temperature sintering is required for SOFCs, bulk and interfacial microstructural changes may occur in the cathode during fabrication.
Titulo: Evaluation of the relationship between cathode microstructure and electrochemical behavior for SOFCs

Sentencas: These changes influence device performance by affecting the various steps of the cathodic reaction and an increased understanding of this relationship may lead to more efficient SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of the relationship between cathode microstructure and electrochemical behavior for SOFCs

Sentencas: Symmetric cells with various microstructures were formed using anneals at temperatures ranging from 1150 to 1325 degrees C for 1 h. Dual beam SEM/FIB (focused ion beam) was used to perform 3-D analysis of the microstructure.
Titulo: Evaluation of the relationship between cathode microstructure and electrochemical behavior for SOFCs

Sentencas: Microstructural features of emphasis include the triple phase boundary length (L-TPB) and pore surface area.
Titulo: Evaluation of the relationship between cathode microstructure and electrochemical behavior for SOFCs

Sentencas: The results were compared with an AC impedance spectroscopy study focusing on charge transfer resistance and oxygen adsorption, A direct relationship between microstructural parameters from an actual cathode and the polarization resistance of the significant elementary steps of the cathodic reaction is established directly from experiment.
Titulo: Evaluation of the relationship between cathode microstructure and electrochemical behavior for SOFCs

Sentencas: It is found that both the charge transfer polarization resistance and the adsorption polarization resistance display a power law relationship with L-TPB and pore surface area, respectively.
Titulo: Evaluation of the relationship between cathode microstructure and electrochemical behavior for SOFCs
